12361", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/12361", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/12361.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/12361.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>Replaces the sync wrappers for device to device operations in verbs_util, with a call to the async function with a callback function. Resolves Issue <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"245192488\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/11725\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/11725/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/11725\">#11725</a></p>\n<p>As mentioned in the issue:<br>\nI think the problem rises because the Sync deviceToDevice operation blocks the thread, preventing the earlier Async Device to Device operation from finishing- which, for some reason, blocks the later operation.</p>\n<p>I've tested this fix in origin/r1.3 since origin/master is currently broken.</p>\n<p>2nd commit only removes the unused functions from verbs_utils. It is not required for validity.</p>\n<p><a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=12075848\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/junshi15\">@junshi15</a> , <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=22274255\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/shamoya\">@shamoya</a> , <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=2613663\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/byronyi\">@byronyi</a> , can you please go over this?</p>", "body_text": "Replaces the sync wrappers for device to device operations in verbs_util, with a call to the async function with a callback function. Resolves Issue #11725\nAs mentioned in the issue:\nI think the problem rises because the Sync deviceToDevice operation blocks the thread, preventing the earlier Async Device to Device operation from finishing- which, for some reason, blocks the later operation.\nI've tested this fix in origin/r1.3 since origin/master is currently broken.\n2nd commit only removes the unused functions from verbs_utils. It is not required for validity.\n@junshi15 , @shamoya , @byronyi , can you please go over this?", "body": "Replaces the sync wrappers for device to device operations in verbs_util, with a call to the async function with a callback function. Resolves Issue #11725 \r\n\r\nAs mentioned in the issue:\r\nI think the problem rises because the Sync deviceToDevice operation blocks the thread, preventing the earlier Async Device to Device operation from finishing- which, for some reason, blocks the later operation.\r\n\r\nI've tested this fix in origin/r1.3 since origin/master is currently broken.\r\n\r\n2nd commit only removes the unused functions from verbs_utils. It is not required for validity. \r\n\r\n@junshi15 , @shamoya , @byronyi , can you please go over this?"}